And lastly there is an example
with else if statements.

00:04:23.570 --> 00:04:25.940
Based on everything that
I've shown you so far,

00:04:25.940 --> 00:04:31.145
you're probably realizing that Java has
a special use for the words if and else.

00:04:31.145 --> 00:04:35.390
They're Java keywords and they're used
to control how the code is executed.

00:04:35.390 --> 00:04:38.220
So you can't use these
as variable names.

00:04:38.220 --> 00:04:41.420
&gt;From the examples that I showed you, you
also may have started to realize that we

00:04:41.420 --> 00:04:44.260
